    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Indeed this was already open. Thanks for closing the other one @Haroenv.\r\n\r\nAs per the solution the problem is that this is related to an option that is in another widget (hits). One quick fix is to be able to identify that there was a post and pre tag that were set, and convert back to `<em>`. The problem is that it might be custom settings, and the user would be surprised to `<em>` instead of it own custom config.\r\n\r\nAnother approach is to have a new independent setting `escapeFacetHighlight` but then it requires to change the `searchForFacetValues` method in the helper, because currently it doesn't support passing custom settings. I think the latter is the best option.",
